a Academy of Information and Communications Technology. [Xinhua/NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. Three China's major telecom operators have been revealed to have built more than 80,000 5G base stations in four months. The recorded first quarter of the year's development was reported as a contributing action to the country's mission to improve its infrastructure development of the super-fast wireless technology. The telecom… October 22, 2019 In "Foreign" By Prince Osuagwu, Hi-Tech Editor Electromagnetic radiation is the new buzz word. Naturally, any mention of ‘radiation’ alarms a random person. It is apparently on this basis a wide claim that the rampaging Coronavirus pandemic, COVID-19, has a root in radiations emitting from 5G facilities like base stations and masts… April 8, 2020 In "Technology" With the roll-out of 5G networks and other new technologies, global companies such as Huawei would continue playing a key role in information and communications technology (ICT) services, said African ICT experts. July 16, 2019 In "News"